The paper discusses the efficiency of autonomous ridesharing systems (ARS) and how user participation affects it. This topic falls under the category of multi-agent systems (cs.MA) as ARS involves multiple agents (vehicles and passengers) interacting with each other. The paper also uses simulations to analyze the impact of user behavior, which falls under the category of control and optimization (cs.CY) and systems and control (cs.SY). The paper also mentions making decisions based on data-driven simulations, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
